author: @nadieirrie5830
text:
Took me a while to realise but now i am getting it.....all of his b-sides are kind of like descriptions of different lovers, like easy happens to be my kind of love- this playful bond that can get deeper but is taken more as a 'i want to hang out with with you because you're a fun person and like being around you, not because you're my lover', Completely is for a lover who is really hurt from someone's actions, somebody who needs the compassion and deep restoring love of their current lover, Can't Get You is for a lover who longs to be loved as deeply as they themselves love their partner, a constant longing for affection from their partner. Dandelion and Roses are descriptions of Puppy Love (similar to Easy but the difference is Dandelion has a childlike feel, the "i take this more seriously than it actually is" instead of Easy's "we are simply having fun") and Bittersweet love that comes with longing for somebody who hurt you but also gave you do many great memories. Flamin Hot Lemon is the crushing love that makes you think that the other person is some kind of higher being, where the lover is indifferent to (Jae here) but even soyou wish they pick you even if they have other options (which may or may not be even true).

Really astounded by how much creativity Jamal has shown with this album, with actively contributing to most of the music in this tracklist. The songs are soooo good, and it's not like typical NCT tracks which i love purely because they are loveable, Jae has made music that i can deeply feel and even relate with, making it all the more loveable, moving and enjoyable. Thank you so much, Jeong YuNo, czennies are now ded because of your abilities. 💚
